<item>
            <title>[LU-6540] too many arguments in a format string in lustre tests, lustre/tests/flock.c</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6540</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Static analysis with cppcheck found the following issue in lustre/tests/flock.c:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Checking lustre/tests/flock.c...&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;lustre/tests/flock.c:178&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;: (warning) printf format string requires 0 parameters but 1 is given.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        fd = open(file, O_RDWR|O_CREAT, (mode_t)0666);&lt;br/&gt;
        if (fd &amp;lt; 0) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                printf(&quot;error open file: %m\n&quot;, file);
                exit(-1);
        }

&lt;p&gt;The %m prints strerror(errno),  but there is no %s specifier for the file.  I believe a modern version GCC  will flag this with a warning too.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Ubuntu 15.04, cppcheck static anaysis + GCC 4.9.2</environment>
